THE	1
LITTLE	1
JACKALS	1
AND	1
THE	1
LION	1
Once	1
there	1
was	1
a	1
great	1
big	1
jungle;	1
and	1
in	1
the	1
jungle	1
there	1
was	1
a	1
great	1
big	1
Lion;	1
and	1
the	1
Lion	1
was	1
king	1
of	1
the	1
jungle.	1
Whenever	1
he	1
wanted	1
anything	1
to	1
eat,	1
all	1
he	1
had	1
to	1
do	1
was	1
to	1
come	1
up	1
out	1
of	1
his	1
cave	1
in	1
the	1
stones	1
and	1
earth	1
and	1
_roar_.	1
When	1
he	1
had	1
roared	1
a	1
few	1
times	1
all	1
the	1
little	1
people	1
of	1
the	1
jungle	1
were	1
so	1
frightened	1
that	1
they	1
came	1
out	1
of	1
their	1
holes	1
and	1
hiding-places	1
and	1
ran,	1
this	1
way	1
and	1
that,	1
to	1
get	1
away.	1
Then,	1
of	1
course,	1
the	1
Lion	1
could	1
see	1
where	1
they	1
were.	1
And	1
he	1
pounced	1
on	1
them,	1
killed	1
them,	1
and	1
gobbled	1
them	1
up.	1
He	1
did	1
this	1
so	1
often	1
that	1
at	1
last	1
there	1
was	1
not	1
a	1
single	1
