alive	1
in	1
the	1
jungle	1
besides	1
the	1
Lion,	1
except	1
two	1
little	1
Jackals,--a	1
little	1
father	1
Jackal	1
and	1
a	1
little	1
mother	1
Jackal.	1
They	1
had	1
run	1
away	1
so	1
many	1
times	1
that	1
they	1
were	1
quite	1
thin	1
and	1
very	1
tired,	1
and	1
they	1
could	1
not	1
run	1
so	1
fast	1
any	1
more.	1
And	1
one	1
day	1
the	1
Lion	1
was	1
so	1
near	1
that	1
the	1
little	1
mother	1
Jackal	1
grew	1
frightened;	1
she	1
said,--	1
"Oh,	1
Father	1
Jackal,	1
Father	1
Jackal!	1
I	1
b'lieve	1
our	1
time	1
has	1
come!	1
the	1
Lion	1
will	1
surely	1
catch	1
us	1
this	1
time!"	1
"Pooh!	1
nonsense,	1
mother!"	1
said	1
the	1
little	1
father	1
Jackal.	1
"Come,	1
we'll	1
run	1
on	1
a	1
bit!"	1
And	1
they	1
ran,	1
ran,	1
ran	1
very	1
fast,	1
and	1
the	1
Lion	1
did	1
not	1
catch	1
them	1
that	1
time.	1
But	1
at	1
last	1
a	1
day	1
came	1
when	1
the	1
Lion	1
was	1
nearer	1
still	1
and	1
the	1
little	1
mother	1
Jackal	1
was	1
frightened	1
almost	1
to	1
death.	1
"Oh,	1
Father	1
Jackal,	1
Father	1
Jackal!"	1
