but	1
the	1
Camel	1
came	1
safely	1
home.	1
THE	1
GULLS	1
OF	1
SALT	1
LAKE	1
The	1
story	1
I	1
am	1
going	1
to	1
tell	1
you	1
is	1
about	1
something	1
that	1
really	1
happened,	1
many	1
years	1
ago.	1
A	1
brave	1
little	1
company	1
of	1
pioneers	1
from	1
the	1
Atlantic	1
coast	1
crossed	1
the	1
Mississippi	1
River	1
and	1
journeyed	1
across	1
the	1
plains	1
of	1
Central	1
North	1
America	1
in	1
big	1
covered	1
wagons	1
with	1
many	1
horses,	1
and	1
finally	1
succeeded	1
in	1
climbing	1
to	1
the	1
top	1
of	1
the	1
great	1
Rockies	1
and	1
down	1
again	1
into	1
a	1
valley	1
in	1
the	1
very	1
midst	1
of	1
the	1
mountains.	1
It	1
was	1
a	1
valley	1
of	1
brown,	1
bare,	1
desert	1
soil,	1
in	1
a	1
climate	1
where	1
almost	1
no	1
rain	1
falls;	1
but	1
the	1
snow	1
on	1
the	1
mountain-tops	1
sent	1
down	1
little	1
streams	1
of	1
pure	1
water,	1
the	1
winds	1
were	1
gentle,	1
and	1
lying	1
like	1
a	1
blue	1
jewel	1
at	1
the	1
foot	1
of	1
the	1
western	1
hills	1
was	1
a	1
marvellous	1
lake	1
of	1
salt	1
water,--an	1
inland	1
sea.	1
So	1
the	1
pioneers	1
settled	1
there	1
and	1
built	1
themselves	1
huts	1
and	1
cabins	1
for	1
the	1
first	1
winter.	1
It	1
had	1
taken	1
them	1
many	1
months	1
to	1
make	1
the	1
terrible	1
journey;	1
many	1
had	1
died	1
of	1
weariness	1
and	1
illness	1
on	1
the	1
way;	1
many	1
died	1
of	1
hardship	1
during	1
the	1
winter;	1
and	1
the	1
provisions	1
they	1
had	1
brought	1
in	1
their	1
wagons	1
were	1
so	1
nearly	1
gone	1
that,	1
by	1
spring,	1
they	1
were	1
living	1
partly	1
on	1
roots,	1
dug	1
from	1
the	1
ground.	1
All	1
their	1
lives	1
now	1
depended	1
on	1
the	1
crops	1
of	1
grain	1
and	1
vegetables	1
which	1
they	1
could	1
raise	1
in	1
the	1
valley.	1
They	1
made	1
the	1
barren	1
land	1
fertile	1
by	1
spreading	1
water	1
from	1
the	1
little	1
streams	1
over	1
