was	1
like	1
beating	1
at	1
the	1
sea.	1
Then	1
they	1
ran	1
and	1
told	1
the	1
terrible	1
news,	1
and	1
all	1
the	1
village	1
came	1
to	1
help.	1
They	1
started	1
fires;	1
they	1
dug	1
trenches	1
and	1
filled	1
them	1
with	1
water;	1
they	1
ran	1
wildly	1
about	1
in	1
the	1
fields,	1
killing	1
what	1
they	1
could.	1
But	1
while	1
they	1
fought	1
in	1
one	1
place	1
new	1
armies	1
of	1
crickets	1
marched	1
down	1
the	1
mountain-sides	1
and	1
attacked	1
the	1
fields	1
in	1
other	1
places.	1
And	1
at	1
last	1
the	1
people	1
fell	1
on	1
their	1
knees	1
and	1
wept	1
and	1
cried	1
in	1
despair,	1
for	1
they	1
saw	1
starvation	1
and	1
death	1
in	1
the	1
fields.	1
A	1
